analysis: The documents primarily focus on amending previous executive orders. The amendments include changes to committee memberships, revisions to sections of existing orders, and adjustments to the responsibilities of various government officials and agencies. Many of the changes involve adding or removing members from committees and councils, or updating position titles and responsibilities. The documents cover a wide range of topics, including national security, economic policy, youth fitness, and equal employment opportunity.
title: Amendments to Existing Executive Orders: Committees, Councils, and Responsibilities
